    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-23T02:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-23T02:34:00-05:00" n="656"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1482: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-23T16:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 23—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your cable of April 19, 3 p.m. I can have 65 members of Service Corps ready to
                    leave Vladivostok May 10. It is necessary in view of the difficulties we are
                    meeting with in the evacuation Czechs that we retain the balance of Corps until
                    all Czechs have arrived Vladivostok. The efforts of the Corps furnished the only
                    reasons upon which successful evacuation of the Czechs can be expected. Please
                    advise as to transport.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
